Sentencas: Tuning semiconductors as an electrolyte for advanced low-temperature fuel cells is an exciting but challenging research subject.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of a Co-Doped SrSnO3-δ-Based Semiconductor as an Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: To realize this, we develop the cobalt-doped SrSnO3 (SrCo0.1Sn0.9O3-delta and SrCo0.2Sn0.8O3-delta) toward an electrolyte, which only permits ions to pass but blocks the electrons simultaneously.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of a Co-Doped SrSnO3-δ-Based Semiconductor as an Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The SrCo0.2Sn0.8O3-delta electrolyte fuel cell has achieved a remarkable performance with a maximum power density of 476 mW cm(-2) and obtained a high ionic conductivity of 0.12 S cm(-1) at a low temperature of 520 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of a Co-Doped SrSnO3-δ-Based Semiconductor as an Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This improved performance is accredited to the bandgap engineering and built-in electric field, which significantly enhanced the ionic transport while suppressing the electronic conduction.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of a Co-Doped SrSnO3-δ-Based Semiconductor as an Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The doped SrCoSnO3-delta perovskite materials demonstrated a high potential for solving the low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (LT-SOFC) material's challenging problems.
